                    <div class="comment_body">
                        After reading through some of these posts I see so many of you STILL think that the hard times and poverty we are experiencing is just a product of a down economy and if somehow we could create more jobs everything would be OK... This is like the Ostrich putting it's head in the sand. So many of you have been so ignorant to what has happened to us as a nation that you cannot see what has happened or how we                        
                                                    <a class="pundits_readmore vertical_color" href="#" onclick="HuffPoUtil.hide(this); HuffPoUtil.show_inline('pundit_comment_text_272778316'); return false;">&nbsp;Read More...</a>
                            <span class="hidden" id="pundit_comment_text_272778316"> got like this. <br> There are a wide variety of people who come here to vent and express opinion and there are many who come here simply to agitate and aren't interested in learning anything. For those of you really interested in why there is such a disparity between the haves and the havenots in this country go back 100 years, you have the internet in front of you search out economic decisions and their results. You will find that early in the 20th century was the first time that the elite tried to take control of society to the point where they alone had the power to choose winners and losers. Men like Theodore Roosevelt, Woodrow Wilson, Franklin D Roosevelt managed to prevent this and develop a system of governance and economics that benefited everyone. &nbsp; <br> Fast forward to the early 1970's and the greed and desire of the elites and their nationalist allies had determined that they had enough of the great society and were losing to much power and profit to the class of people created as a result of it... The great middle class. In their arrogance they decided that only they should be determining the direction of this country and that it's resources should serve them instead of being wasted on the many in society that they deemed "inferior". A 50 year strategy was devised that would turn around every societal advance made by those early Progressives and would leave the powerful in charge with no way to oppose them, a fundamental overthrow of the American democracy.&nbsp; <br> It was to begin with Nixon and it indeed was developed by the men working around him. Nixon however, did not understand the need to be covert and patient and thus a scandal developed that prevented real implementation of the effort to take control until 1980. At this point the GOP was completely under control of certain elites and the GOP was all in with their agenda which promised to end in a two class society with them permanently representing the ruling class. First, control the people (sheep) through a separate media owned and controlled by the movement, second, bring the government to bankruptcy and blame it on social welfare programs, third, Break the power of the labor unions, fourth restrict the vote.... &nbsp;Sound familiar? look at what was done to break the unions and eliminate high wage skill jobs during the early 2000's and late 90's... there is your clue to why you</span>
